                <head>123. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On October 5, 1960, the President approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    Action No. 2315, in which the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> concurred in
                    the recommendation of the Secretary of Defense that a total of 14 Polaris
                    submarines be authorized for construction, and that long lead-time planning and
                    procurement actions be authorized to permit construction of 5 additional Polaris
                    submarines. (Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> (Miscellaneous) Files: Lot 66 D 95, Records of
                    Action by the National Security Council) <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    Action No. 2315 superseded <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No.
                    2168–b; see <ref target="#d82fn4">footnote 4, Document 82</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
